cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with problems related to computational geometry, such as covering points by lines, maximum point coverage by lines, and minimum-link covering/spanning tours. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the complexity of these problems, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper involves combinatorial optimization, which could place it in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
